  "prompt": "What would you do and how would you feel if you found out you had a child you'd never met?",
  "response": "If I were a person and found out I had a child I'd never met, I might experience a whirlwind of emotions. Initially, there would likely be shock and disbelief at the revelation. Questions about the child's well-being, upbringing, and how to connect with them would flood my mind. \n\nI would probably feel a mix of excitement and anxiety about the prospect of meeting this child and understanding their life. The thought of missed milestones and experiences could bring feelings of sadness or regret. At the same time, there might be a strong desire to establish a relationship and make up for lost time.\n\nUltimately, I would likely want to approach the situation with care, ensuring that the child\u2019s needs and feelings are prioritized while trying to navigate the complexities of such a significant life event. Open communication with them, if they were receptive, would be important in building trust and a potential bond.",
